spec.brief: PL kernel for QR decomposition cfloat version.

parameters.name: PowUnroll
parameters.description: Power2 of RowsA Size, default power2(10) = 1024

parameters.name: PowFoldRow
parameters.description: Power2 of fold Rows Size, default power2(2) = 4

parameters.name: PowNCU
parameters.description: Power2 of compute unit(CU) number, default power2(5) = 32

parameters.name: T
parameters.description: the data type of the complex<type> matrix entries

spec.brief: PL kernel for QR decomposition float version.

parameters.name: PowUnroll
parameters.description: Power2 of RowsA Size, default power2(10) = 1024

parameters.name: PowFoldRow
parameters.description: Power2 of fold Rows Size, default power2(2) = 4

parameters.name: PowNCU
parameters.description: Power2 of compute unit(CU) number, default power2(5) = 32

parameters.name: T

parameters.name: LowerTriangularL

spec.brief: matrixMultiply entry point function for calculating matrix power.

parameters.name: TransposeFormA1
parameters.description: Defines if the first matix is transposed before the multiplication. Valid values are: NoTranspose, Transpose, ConjugateTranspose

parameters.name: TransposeFormA2
parameters.description: Defines if the second matix is transposed before the multiplication.

parameters.name: RowsA
parameters.description: Defines the number of rows in the A matrix

parameters.name: ColsA
parameters.description: Defines the number of columns in the A matrix

parameters.name: RowsC
parameters.description: Defines the number of rows in the C matrix

parameters.name: ColsC
parameters.description: Defines the number of columns in the C matrix

spec.brief: QRF, to computes the full QR factorization (QR decomposition) of input matrix A, A=QR, producing orthogonal output matrix Q and upper-triangular matrix R.

parameters.name: TransposedQ
parameters.description: Selects whether Q is output in transposed form

parameters.name: RowsA
parameters.description: Number of rows in input matrix A

parameters.name: ColsA
parameters.description: Number of columns in input matrix A
